								<div id="h_EXTAFFAIRS-DS">
								<p><a href="javascript:ShowHide('EXTAFFAIRS-DS')">Office of the Deputy Secretary for External Affairs and Relations</a></p>
								</div>
								<div id="EXTAFFAIRS-DS" class="iL1">
									<p class="OfficeDesc">The Deputy 
									Secretary for External Affairs and Relations 
									advises and assists the Senate Secretary in the 
									formulation and implementation of external 
									affairs and relations’ policies and programs of 
									the Senate. The office aims to institutionalize 
									an efficient system of networking and 
									interaction with the executive branch, the 
									academe, the private sector, NGOs, national and 
									international organizations.</p>
									<table>
										<tr>
											<th class="OfficeLeftCol"></th>
											<th></th>
										</tr>
										<tr>
											<td>Head of Office</td>
											<td>Enrique Luis D. Papa, Deputy 
											Secretary</td>
										</tr>
										<tr>
											<td>Office Address</td>
											<td>4th Flr., Senate of the 
											Philippines, Roxas Blvd., Pasay City</td>
										</tr>
										<tr>
											<td>Contact Numbers</td>
											<td>(632) 8-552-6601 to 6670 loc. 4101 
											to 03, (632) 8-552-6804</td>
										</tr>
									</table>
								</div>
							
								<div id="h_EXTAFFAIRS-ED">
								<p><a href="javascript:ShowHide('EXTAFFAIRS-ED')">Office of the Executive Director for External Affairs and Relations</a></p>
								</div>
								<div id="EXTAFFAIRS-ED" class="iL1">
									<p class="OfficeDesc">The Executive 
									Director for External Affairs and Relations 
									assists the EAR Deputy Secretary in the 
									formulation and implementation of external 
									affairs and relations’ policies and programs of 
									the Senate. The office oversees the supervision 
									of all the units under the External Affairs and 
									Relations. Under this office are four services 
									whose functions are designed to carry out 
									assigned task.</p>
									<table>
										<tr>
											<th class="OfficeLeftCol"></th>
											<th></th>
										</tr>
										<tr>
											<td>Head of Office</td>
											<td>Diana Lynn L. Cruz, Executive 
											Director</td>
										</tr>
										<tr>
											<td>Office Address</td>
											<td>4th Flr., Senate of the 
											Philippines, Roxas Blvd., Pasay City</td>
										</tr>
										<tr>
											<td>Contact Numbers</td>
											<td>(632) 8-552-6601 to 6670 loc. 4107 
											&amp; 4108, 
											(632) 8-552-6740, (632) 8-552-6827 </td>
										</tr>
									</table>
								</div>
							
								<div id="h_LIAISON">
								<p><a href="javascript:ShowHide('LIAISON')">Executive-Legislative Liaison Service</a></p>
								</div>
								<div id="LIAISON" class="iL1">
									<p class="OfficeDesc">Legislative-Executive Liaison Service promotes 
									harmonious and productive relations among the 
									Senate, the Executive Branch, and other branches 
									and instrumentalities of government, thus, 
									ensuring cooperation and coordination in the 
									formulation and implementation of bills. It 
									facilitates networking and consensus building 
									between the Senate and all departments of the 
									Executive Branch as it relates to legislation.</p>
									<table>
										<tr>
											<th class="OfficeLeftCol"></th>
											<th></th>
										</tr>
										<tr>
											<td>Head of Office</td>
											<td>Rommel L. Escudero, (OIC)</td>
										</tr>
										<tr>
											<td>Office Address</td>
											<td>4th Flr., Senate of the 
											Philippines, Roxas Blvd., Pasay City</td>
										</tr>
										<tr>
											<td>Contact Numbers</td>
											<td>(632) 8-552-6601 to 6670 loc. 4109 
											&amp; 4110, 
											(632) 8-552-6825</td>
										</tr>
									</table>
								</div>
							
								<div id="h_LINKAGES">
								<p><a href="javascript:ShowHide('LINKAGES')">Institutional Linkages Service</a></p>
								</div>
								<div id="LINKAGES" class="iL1">
									<p class="OfficeDesc">Institutional 
									Linkages Service enhances relations between the 
									Senate and the non-government organizations by 
									providing a forum for effective and continuous 
									dialogue to broaden the people’s participation 
									in the legislative process. It serves as a 
									linkage between the legislators and the various 
									sectors such as the academe, NGOs, diplomatic, 
									religious and business communities and 
									socio-civic and international organizations.</p>
									<table>
										<tr>
											<th class="OfficeLeftCol"></th>
											<th></th>
										</tr>
										<tr>
											<td>Head of Office</td>
											<td>Julieta J. Cervo, Director III</td>
										</tr>
										<tr>
											<td>Office Address</td>
											<td>4th Flr., Senate of the 
											Philippines, Roxas Blvd., Pasay City</td>
										</tr>
										<tr>
											<td>Contact Numbers</td>
											<td>(632) 8-552-6601 to 6670 loc. 4104 
											to 4106, 
											(632) 8-552-6826</td>
										</tr>
									</table>
								</div>
							
								<div id="h_SPECIALSVC">
								<p><a href="javascript:ShowHide('SPECIALSVC')">Special Services</a></p>
								</div>
								<div id="SPECIALSVC" class="iL1">
									<p class="OfficeDesc">Special Services 
									develops and implements various staff 
									enhancement program such as sports and cultural 
									development as well as organization and conduct 
									of outreach programs for the Senate employees. 
									It provides briefings and orientation programs 
									for the students and the general public. Also, 
									it provides auxiliary and ad hoc services to the 
									Senators, staff and employees of the Senate.</p>
